#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:177
msgid "Effects"
msgstr "Efectos"

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:180
msgid ""
"The top part of the column uses the {ref}`Standard Effects Mapping "
"<controller-effects-mapping>`. Pressing the top encoder acts as the effect "
"focus button. When no effect is focused, the buttons are red. When holding "
"the top encoder to choose an effect to focus, the buttons are green. When an"
" effect is focused, the buttons are amber."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:187
msgid "The fader acts as the mix knob."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:189
msgid ""
"The bottom buttons assign the effect unit to different input channels and "
"light up red. On the two deck layouts, from top to bottom, they assign the "
"effect unit to deck 1, deck 2, main mix, and headphones. On the four effect "
"unit layouts, they assign the effect unit to decks 1-4 going down the "
"column. You can look down a column to see which decks an effect unit is "
"assigned. You can look across a row to see which effect units are assigned "
"to a deck. When shift is pressed, the bottom two buttons switch to "
"controlling the routing buttons for the main and headphones channels and "
"light up amber."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:199
msgid "The bottom encoders are not mapped in the 4 effect unit layout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:201
msgid "Effect unit focusing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:204
msgid ""
"In addition to focusing one effect in a unit at a time with the "
"{ref}`Standard Effects Mapping <controller-effects-mapping>`, the Xone "
"K1/K2/K3 has another mode for focusing a whole effect unit. This allows for "
"controlling the parameters of all 3 effects in the unit at a time. This mode"
" is only available on the 4 effect unit layouts. To access it, press the "
"Layer button in the bottom left. Press one of the top encoders to choose "
"which effect unit to focus."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:212
msgid ""
"In this mode, each horizontal row of knobs and buttons controls one effect. "
"The knobs control the parameters of the effects. Turning any of the knobs "
"with shift loads different effects. The button in the leftmost column "
"controls the enable button of the effect and turns amber when it is on. The "
"rest of the buttons control the button parameters of the effect and turn "
"green when active (not all effects have button parameters). The faders still"
" control the dry/wet knobs and the bottom button grid still controls the "
"routing buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:221
msgid ""
"To get back to controlling all 4 effect units, press the Layer button again."
" The next time Layer is pressed, the effect unit that was focused before "
"will be remembered (but it will not be remembered after restarting Mixxx)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:226
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr "Solución de problemas"

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:229
msgid ""
"If general functionality or supershift are not working, double check that "
"Latch Layers is turned off and MIDI CH is selected. If you are using Xone "
"K3, also check that the controller is running firmware v1.0.4 r 93846. Refer"
" to the [Xone K2 manual](https://www.allen-"
"heath.com/content/uploads/2023/06/XoneK2_UG_AP8509_3.pdf) page 12 for "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:236
msgid "Known Issues"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:239
msgid "There are a few known issues with the Xone K1/K2/K3 firmware:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:241
msgid ""
"Since there is no way for Mixxx to ask the controller about the positions of"
" all the knobs and faders when Mixxx starts, they are out of sync with the "
"state of Mixxx until they are first moved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:244
msgid ""
"When the USB connection is interrupted and the controller stays powered on, "
"such as leaving the controller plugged into a powered USB hub and "
"disconnecting the hub from the computer, the controller will not send MIDI "
"input until it is powered down (unplugged) and plugged back in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/allen_heath_xone_k2_k1.md:249
msgid ""
"If you would like these issues to be fixed, please let [Allen & Heath "
"Support](https://www.allen-heath.com/support/) know."
msgstr ""
